│ An LLVM developer is seeking assistance with a bug that      │
│ causes a miscompilation on the AArch64 target. The issue     │
│ stems from an incorrect transformation in the                │
│ `VectorCombine` pass, where a `zext` instruction is          │
│ aggressively sunk through a logical right shift (`lshr`).    │
│ This transformation can introduce `poison` values when the   │
│ type is shrunk to a single bit (`i1`), as shifting an `i1`   │
│ by any non-zero amount is undefined.                         │
│                                                              │
│ To address this, I will implement a patch that adds a guard  │
│ to the `shrinkType` function in `VectorCombine.cpp`. This    │
│ guard will prevent the sinking of a `zext` through a shift   │
│ operation if the destination type is `i1` and the shift      │
│ amount is not a known zero. This ensures the transformation  │
│ is only applied when it is guaranteed to be safe, thus       │
│ resolving the bug.                                           │
